dentità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo R. Henzel, 2016-11-07\" src=\"ISic000019-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of ILPalermo (Bivona) checked against the photograph\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan> Bivona: Auṛẹ; Mommsen: AV̂R \u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>As Bivona notes, Mommsen in CIL chose to unify this fragment with one recorded by Gualtherus and Fazello (ISic001896, on a piece of an architrave, re-used as a church step, and which read: IMP. M. AVRELIO . ANTONINO . AVG...). However. Torremuzza described that piece separately from this one, which he placed in the courtyard of the Palazzo Senatorio, and there seems no obvious reason to conflate them.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1762 13 no.xxiv \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002085\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Mommsen 1883 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/650789\" target=\"_blank\">7277\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bivona 1970 19 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002142\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Tall and very narrow letters, fairly crudely carved, 